subject: p16334516
Findings: A longstanding left upper lobe oval nodule has been present since at least and has not changed since at least when a Chest CT report termed it benign. Sclerosis at the right first costochondral junction as well as post-surgical changes from a wedge resection in the right upper lobe are all stable since. The cardiomediastinal silhouette and hila are normal. There is no pleural effusion and no pneumothorax. Mild pulmonary vascular congestion is chronic or recurrent.
Impression: No acute cardiothoracic process including no evidence of pneumonia.
